{"title_page": "List of ships of the Indian Navy", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2012}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2012}}\nThis is a '''list of ships of the Indian Navy'''. It covers both the pre-independence [[Royal Indian Navy]]<ref>{{cite web|title=genesis |url=http://indiannavy.nic.in/genesis.htm |publisher=Official Indian Navy Cite |accessdate=29 October 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110111202914/http://indiannavy.nic.in/genesis.htm |archivedate=11 January 2011 }}</ref>  and the post-independence [[Indian Navy]]. This article is incomplete, editors are welcome to contribute to expanding this list.\n\n==Current ships==\n\n{{main|List of active Indian Navy ships}}\n\n==Historical ships==\n'''Note:'''  Prior to 1950, Indian naval ships carried the prefix HMIS (\"His Majesty's Indian Ship\") as the Indian Armed Forces were under the British Crown. After the declaration of the Republic of India on 26 January 1950, the prefix became INS (\"Indian Naval Ship\").\n\n===Aircraft carriers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Ship\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:5%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Pennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n|{{INS|Vikrant|R11|6}}\n|R11\n|[[Majestic-class aircraft carrier|''Majestic'' class]]\n|4 March 1961\n|31 January 1997<ref name=Hiranandani>Hiranandani G.M, Transition to Eminence - The Indian Navy 1976 \u2013 90; pub Lancer New Dehli 2005, {{ISBN|978-81-7062-266-6}}</ref>\n|Converted to IMS-Indian Museum Ship briefly but subsequently scrapped in 2014.\n|formerly '''HMS ''Hercules''''' although never commissioned into the Royal Navy.\n|-\n|[[INS Viraat]]\n|R22\n|[[Centaur-class aircraft carrier|Centaur class]]\n|12 May 1987\n|6 March 2017\n|Yet to be Decided\n|\n|}\n\n===Submarines===\n{{see also|List of submarines of the Indian Navy}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Boat\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:5%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Pennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Nuclear Submarines\n|-\n|[[Soviet submarine K-43|INS ''Chakra'']]\n| S71\n|[[Charlie-class submarine|''Charlie'' class]]\n|1 September 1987\n|Returned to Soviet Union in January 1991\n|Scrapped in Russia.\n|leased from the Soviet Union.\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Conventional Submarines\n|-\n|{{INS|Khanderi|1968|6}}\n|S22\n|{{sclass-|Kalvari|submarine|4||1967}}\n|6 December 1968\n|18 October 1989<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|scrapped but sail fin on display\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Kalvari|S23|6}}\n|S23\n|{{sclass-|Kalvari|submarine|4||1967}}\n|8 December 1967\n|31 May 1996<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|scrapped but sail fin on display\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Kursura|S20|6}}\n|S20\n|{{sclass-|Kalvari|submarine|4||1967}}\n|18 December 1969\n|27 September 2001<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Converted to Museum Ship at [[Ramakrishna Mission Beach]], [[Visakhapatnam]].\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Karanj|S21|6}}\n|S21\n|{{sclass-|Kalvari|submarine|4||1967}}\n|4 September 1969\n|1 August 2003<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Vagsheer|S43|6}}\n|S43\n|[[Vela-class submarine|''Vela'' class]]\n|26 December 1974