6|6}}\n|T56\n|[[Seaward-class defense boats|Seaward defence boat]]\n|\n|2008\u20132009\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Seasand|T59|6}}\n|T59\n|[[Seaward-class defense boats|Seaward defence boat]]\n|\n|7 September 2009\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Searock|T60|6}}\n|T60\n|[[Seaward-class defense boats|Seaward defence boat]]\n|\n|7 September 2009\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Seastorm|T58|6}}\n|T58\n|[[Seaward-class defense boats|Seaward defence boat]]\n|\n|20 July 2010\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[INS Tarasa (T63)|INS ''Tarasa'']]\n|T63\n|[[Trinkat-class patrol vessel|''Trinkat'' class]]\n|24 August 2001\n|7 November 2014\n|Transferred to [[Seychelles Coast Guard]] as [[PS Constant]]\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of active Indian Navy ships]] \u2013 for a complete list of all ships and submarines currently in service with the Indian Navy.\n*[[List of submarines of the Indian Navy]]\n*[[Aircraft of the Indian Navy]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==Sources==\n*Collins, J.T.E. [http://www.ibiblio.org/hyperwar/UN/India/RIN/index.html ''The Royal Indian Navy, 1939\u20131945]''. Official History of the Indian Armed Forces In the Second World War. New Delhi: Combined Inter-Services Historical Section (India & Pakistan), 1964.\n*Parkes, Oscar. ''Jane's Fighting Ships 1931''. Newton Abbot, Devon, UK:Davis & Charles Reprints, 1931 (1973 reprint). {{ISBN|0-7153-5849-9}}.\n*{{cite book |last= Singh|first= Satyindra|date=1992 |title= Blueprint to Bluewater, the Indian Navy, 1951\u201365|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8PLeQ8sM06kC&pg=PA72&lpg=PA72&dq=INS+Mysore+cruiser+pennant+number&source=bl&ots=HuvthXRpCh&sig=8HV809O7fdXn-mjK1PybMnh5nyk&hl=en&sa=X&ei=fJv4U9qzAqmwigK9qoDoCw&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=INS%20Mysore%20cruiser%20pennant%20number&f=false|publisher=[[Lancer Publishers & Distributors]] |page=72 |isbn=978-81-7062-148-5 |accessdate=23 August 2014 }}\n* {{cite book | last1=Rohwer|first1=J\u00fcrgen|last2=Hummelchen|first2=Gerhard|title=Chronology of the War at Sea 1939\u20131945|year=1992|publish