ally-brought-to-surface-1993975|accessdate=20 June 2014|work=DNA|date=7 June 2014}}</ref> she was decommissioned in March 2017 and disposed of at sea that June.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Rajput|first1=Rashmi|title=Navy sinks \u2018graveyard\u2019 INS Sindhurakshak|url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/navy-sinks-graveyard-ins-sindhurakshak-4828999/|accessdate=15 October 2017|work=Indian Express|date=5 September 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Cruisers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Ship\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:5%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Pennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Cruisers\n|-\n|[[INS Delhi (1948)|INS ''Delhi'']] <br/><small>Originally commissioned as '''HMIS ''Delhi'''''</small>\n|C74\n|[[Leander-class cruiser (1931)|''Leander'' class]]\n|5 July 1948\n|30 June 1978<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Scrapped\n|Purchased from the U.K. Formerly [[HMS Achilles (70)|HMS ''Achilles'']] of the [[Battle of the River Plate]] fame. Turrets on Display at [[Devonport Naval Base]], Auckland, New Zealand, and at [[Indian Military Academy]], Dehradun, India.\n|-\n|[[INS Mysore (C60)|INS ''Mysore'']]\n|C60\n|[[Fiji class cruiser|''Fiji'' class]]\n|29 August 1957\n|20 August 1985<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Scrapped\n|Purchased from the U.K. Formerly [[HMS Nigeria (60)|HMS ''Nigeria'']].\n|}\n\n===Destroyers===\n{{main|List of destroyers of the Indian Navy}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Ship\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:5%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Pennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Destroyers\n|-\n|[[HMS Rotherham (H09)|INS ''Rajput'']]\n|D141\n|[[Q and R-class destroyer|''R'' class]]\n| 28 July 1949\n|30 June 1973<ref name=Triumph>Hiranandani G.M, Transition to Triumph - The Indian Navy 1965 \u2013 75; pub Lancer Publishers LLC 2010, {{ISBN|978-1-897829-69-1}}</ref>\n|scrapped 1979\n|\n|-\n|[[HMS Redoubt (H41)|INS ''Ranjit'']]\n|\n|[[Q and R-class destroyer|''R'' class]]\n|4 July 1949\n|30 September 1975<ref name=Triumph/>\n|scrapped 1979\n|\n|-\n|[[HMS Raider (H15)|INS ''Rana'']]\n|D115\n|[[Q and R-class destroyer|''R'' class]]\n|9 September 1949\n|30 September 1971<ref name=Triumph/>\n|scrapped 1979\n|\n|-\n|[[ORP \u015al\u0105zak (L26)|INS ''Godavari'']]\n|D92\n|[[Hunt-class destroyer|Hunt class]]\n|27 April 1953\n|31 Aug 1976<ref name=\"Hiranandani\"/>\n|scrapped 1979\n|leased and then purchased from the Royal Navy. Formerly '''HMS ''Bedale'''''. Was operated by Polish Navy during World War II as [[ORP \u015al\u0105zak (L26)|ORP ''\u015al\u0105zak'']].\n|-\n|[[INS Gomati (D93)|INS ''Gomati'']]\n|D93\n|[[Hunt-class destroyer|Hunt class]]\n|24 April 1953\n|31 May 1972<ref name=Triumph/>\n|scrapped 1975\n|leased and then purchased from the Royal Navy. Formerly [[HMS Lamerton (L88)|HMS ''Lamerton'']].\n|-\n|[[INS Ganga (D94)|INS ''Ganga'']]\n|D94\n|[[Hunt-class destroyer|Hunt class]]\n|18 June 1953\n|31 July 1972<ref name=Triumph/>\n|scrapped 1975\n|leased and then purchased from the Royal Navy. Formerly [[HMS Chiddingfold (L31)|HMS ''Chiddingfold'']].\n|}\n\n===Frigates===\n{{main|List of frigates of the Indian Navy}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Ship\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:5%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Pennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Frigates\n|-\n|[[List of River-class frigates|HMIS ''Tamar'']]\n|K262\n|[[River-class frigate|''River'' class]]\n|1946\n|Dec 1946\n|Constructive Total Loss after running aground off [[Hainan Island]]\n|was previously '''HMS ''Aire''''' prior to Indian service.\n|-\n|[[List of River-class frigates|HMIS ''Neza'']]\n|K239\n|[[River-class frigate|''River'' class]]\n|1946\n|1947\n|Returned to the Royal Navy in April 1947. Scrapped 1955.\n|Served as '''HMS ''Test''''' in the Royal Navy before transfer to India.\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Shamsher|K392|6}}\n|K392\n|[[River-class frigate|''River'' class]]\n|1945\n|1947\n|Transferred to Pakistan and served as PNS ''Shamsher''. Scrapped 1959.\n|Served as '''HMS ''Nadder''''' in the Royal Navy before transfer to India.\n|-\n|[[PNS Zulfiqar (K265)|HMIS ''Dhanush'']]\n|K265\n|[[River-class frigate|''River'' class]]\n|1945\n|1948\n|Transferred to Pakistan and served as PNS ''Dhanush''.\n|Served as '''HMS ''Deveron''''' in the Royal Navy before transfer to India.\n|-\n|[[List of River-class frigates|HMIS ''Kukri'']]<br/><small>renamed '''INS ''Kukri''''' post republic.</small>\n|K243\n|[[River-class frigate|''River'' class]]\n|1946\n|1951\n|Converted to survey vessel post republic. Recommissioned as '''INS ''Investigator''''' <ref name=\"insurvey\"/>\n|Served as '''{{HMS|Trent|K243|6}}''' in the Royal Navy before being transferred to India.\n|-\n|{