rd-class frigate|''Leopard'' class]]\n|24 May 1960\n|22 Dec 1992<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Broken Up 1992\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Betwa|1959|6}}\n|F39\n|[[Leopard-class frigate|''Leopard'' class]]\n|8 December 1960\n|31 December 1991<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Broken Up 1988\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Nilgiri|F33|6}}\n|F33\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n|23 June 1972\n|31 May 1996<ref name=Hiranandani/>\n|Sunk on 24 April 1997, by a Sea Eagle AShM fired from a Sea Harrier Frs Mk.51 of the Indian Navy.\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Himgiri|F34|6}}\n|F34\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n|23 November 1974\n|6 May 2005\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Udaygiri|F35|6}}\n|F35\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n| 18 February 1976\n| 24 August 2007\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Dunagiri|F36|6}}\n|F36\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n|5 May 1977\n|20 October 2010\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Vindhyagiri|F42|6}}\n|F42\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n|8 July 1981\n|14 Jun 2012\n|Collided with a merchant ship while in Mumbai harbour on 30 January 2011; sank after on-board fire. No casualties. Re-floated and decommissioned with full honours in 2012.\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Krishna|F46|6}}\n|F46\n|[[Leander-class frigate|''Leander'' class]]\n|22 August 1995\n|24 May 2012\n|\n|Purchased as a cadet training ship from the Royal Navy. Was previously '''HMS ''Andromeda'''''.\n|-\n|{{INS|Taragiri|F41|6}}\n|F41\n|[[Nilgiri-class frigate (1972)|''Nilgiri'' class]]\n|16 May 1980\n|27 June 2013\n|-\n|{{INS|Godavari|F20|6}}\n|F20\n|[[Godavari-class frigate|''Godavari'' class]]\n|10 December 1983\n|23 December 2015\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Ganga|F22|6}}\n|F22\n|[[Godavari-class frigate|''Godavari'' class]]\n|30 December 1985\n|22 March 2018\n|\n|\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Sloops (later reclassified as frigates)\n|-\n|[[Anchusa-class sloop|HMIS Elphinstone]]\n|\n|[[Anchusa-class sloop|''Anchusa'' class]]\n|May 1922\n|\n|wrecked on Nicobar Islands 29 J