'' class]] || 15 May 1945 || 1946 || returned to Royal Navy and sold to the [[Royal Thai Navy|Thai Navy]] as '''HTMS ''Bangpakong''''' ||\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Sind|K274|6}} || K274 || [[Flower-class corvette|''Flower'' class]] || 24 August 1945 || 1946 || returned to Royal Navy and sold to the Thai Navy as '''HTMS ''Prasae''''' ||\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Mahratta|K395|6}} || K395 || [[Flower-class corvette|''Flower'' class]] || 1946 ||  || Constructive total loss after running aground in 1947. ||\n|-\n| {{HMIS|Assam|K306|6}} || K306 || [[Flower-class corvette|''Flower'' class]] || 19 February 1945 || 1947 || returned to Royal Navy and scrapped ||\n|-\n| {{HMIS|Punjab|J239|6}} || J239 || [[Bathurst-class corvette|''Bathurst'' class]] || 20 March 1942 || 1949 || Transferred to Pakistan post-partition ||\n|-\n| {{HMIS|Bombay|J249|6}}<br/><small>renamed '''INS ''Bombay''''' post republic.</small> || J249 || [[Bathurst-class corvette|''Bathurst'' class]] || 24 April 1942 || 1960 || scrapped || Was involved in defence during the [[Attack on Sydney Harbour]]\n|-\n| {{HMIS|Bengal|J243|6}}<br/><small>renamed '''INS ''Bengal''''' post republic.</small> || J243 || [[Bathurst-class corvette|''Bathurst'' class]] || 8 August 1942 || 1960 || scrapped ||Sank the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]] commerce raider ''[[H\u014dkoku Maru]]'' in 1942 while in Indian service.\n|-\n| {{HMIS|Madras|J237|6}}<br/><small>renamed '''INS ''Madras''''' post republic.</small> || J237 || [[Bathurst-class corvette|''Bathurst'' class]] || 12 May 1942 || 1960 || scrapped ||\n|-\n| {{INS|Arnala|P68|6}} || P68 || [[Arnala-class corvette|''Arnala'' class]] || 29 June 1972 || 9 April 1999 || ||\n|-\n| {{INS|Androth|P69|6}} || P69 || [[Arnala-class corvette|''Arnala'' class]] || 30 June 1972 || 9 April 1999<ref name=Hiranandani/> || ||\n|-\n| {{INS|Anjadip|P73|6}} || P73 || [[Arnala-class corvette|''Arnala'' class]] || 23 December 1972 || 13 December 2003<ref name=Hiranandani/> || ||\n|-\n| {{INS|Andaman|P74|6}} || P74 || [[Arnala-c