ennant\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:15%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Class\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Commissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:10%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Decommissioned\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:12%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Fate\n! style=\"text-align:left; width:25%;background-color:#3399FF;\"|Notes\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background: lavender;\" | Offshore Patrol Vessel\n|-\n|{{HMIS|RAMDAS||6}}<ref name=\"rin3945\"/>\n|\n|requsitioned armed merchant ship <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mail-archive.com/goanet@lists.goanet.org/msg01659.html |title=[Goanet] SS Ramdas |date=2 August 2006}}</ref>\n|1940\n|1945\n|returned to merchant service.\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Jamnagar||6}}<ref name=\"inthewake\">In the Wake, E C Streatfeild-James</ref>\n|\n|requisitioned armed merchant ship\n|1940\n|1947\n|sold and became M/V ''Hellenic Bulbul''.\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Ratnagiri||6}}<ref name=\"inthewake\"/>\n|\n|requisitioned armed merchant ship\n|1940\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Hiravati||6}}<ref name=\"inthewake\"/>\n|\n|requisitioned armed merchant ship\n|1940\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Prabhavati||6}}<ref name=\"inthewake\"/>\n|\n|requisitioned armed merchant ship\n|1940\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Dipavati||6}} <ref name=\"rinr\">{{cite web |url=http://www.unithistories.com/officers/RINR_officers.html |title=Royal Indian Naval Reserve (RINR) Officers 1939\u20131945 }}</ref>\n|\n|auxiliary patrol vessel\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{HMIS|Sonvati||6}}<ref name=\"admwardiary\">{{cite web |url=http://www.naval-history.net/xDKWD-EF1942.htm |title= ADMIRALTY WAR DIARIES of WORLD WAR 2 EAST INDIES FLEET - January to March 1942. |work=[[Admiralty]]}}</ref>\n|\n|auxiliary patrol vessel\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|{{INS|Sarayu|P54|6}}\n|P54\n|[[Sukanya-class patrol vessel|''Sukanya'' class]]\n|8 October 1991\n|2000\n|Sold to Sri Lanka in 2000 and in service as the flagship of [[Sri Lanka Navy]], [[SLNS Sayura|SLNS ''Sayura'']] \n|\n|-\n! colspan=\"7